schema.name: event
schema.title: Event
schema.description: The event name that triggers this set action.

schema.name: entity
schema.title: Entity
schema.description: The entity from where the path starts. If unset, this entity is used.

schema.name: path
schema.title: Path
schema.description: The path to set when the event fires.

schema.name: value
schema.title: Value
schema.description: The value to set the property to.

schema.name: key
schema.title: Key
schema.description: The keyboard key that will fire events

schema.name: keyDownEvent
schema.title: Key Down Event
schema.description: The event fired when the specified key is pressed

schema.name: keyRepeatEvent
schema.title: Key Repeat Event
schema.description: The event fired when the specified key registers a repeat press after the initial press

schema.name: keyUpEvent
schema.title: Key Up Event
schema.description: The event fired when the specified key is released

keys.title: Keys
keys.description: The set of keyboard keys that are configured to fire events

startEvent.title: Start Event
startEvent.description: Event that starts the VR session.

endEvent.title: End Event
endEvent.description: Event that ends the VR session.

space.title: Space
space.description: The tracking space for the VR session.

availableEvent.title: Available Event
availableEvent.description: Fired when a VR session becomes available.

unavailableEvent.title: Unvailable Event
unavailableEvent.description: Fired when a VR session becomes unavailable.

startEvent.title: Start Event
startEvent.description: Fired when a VR session starts.

endEvent.title: End Event
endEvent.description: Fired when a VR session starts.

camera.title: Camera
camera.description: The camera controlled by this first person view. It should be a child of the entity to which this script is assigned. If no camera is assigned, the script will create one for you.

deadZone.title: Dead Zone
deadZone.description: Radial thickness of inner dead zone of the virtual joysticks. This dead zone ensures the virtual joysticks report a value of 0 even if a touch deviates a small amount from the initial touch.

turnSpeed.title: Turn Speed
turnSpeed.description: Maximum turn speed in degrees per second

radius.title: Radius
radius.description: The radius of the virtual joystick in CSS pixels.

doubleTapInterval.title: Double Tap Interval
doubleTapInterval.description: The time in milliseconds between two taps of the right virtual joystick for a double tap to register. A double tap will trigger a jump.

deadZoneLow.title: Low Dead Zone
deadZoneLow.description: Radial thickness of inner dead zone of pad's joysticks. This dead zone ensures that all pads report a value of 0 for each joystick axis when untouched.

deadZoneHigh.title: High Dead Zone
deadZoneHigh.description: Radial thickness of outer dead zone of pad's joysticks. This dead zone ensures that all pads can reach the -1 and 1 limits of each joystick axis.

turnSpeed.title: Turn Speed
turnSpeed.description: Maximum turn speed in degrees per second
